StoryAsset.name: Short Post Match Cup Leg 1 of 2 Rounds

keyValuePair.Value: Have you missed your chance, losing at home?

%1s are usually so strong at home so today's defeat will be a big disappointment. How do you rate your chances of going through? What will you need to do better now in the away leg to give yourselves hope?
It will be another tight game.

There wasn't much between the two sides here and I'm not sure being at home in the first leg was an advantage for us. It's only half-time, right? Let's not worry too much about this result. We know we can improve in the second leg.
We can score goals in the return.

It was a disappointment for us from an attacking point of view. %1s defended very well and denied us space around their penalty box. I hope they'll come at us more in the next game and that might mean things are more open and the boys will be able to take advantage.
They crowded us out.

Fair play to them. They taught us a bit of a lesson, crowding us out in all the important areas. Our boys just couldn't get a foothold in the game. Now we know what we have to do, though. We'll make plans and our lads will be better over there. We're not out of it yet.
Is that your chance gone?
You talked before the game about the importance of taking a lead into the second leg. But you've been well beaten here, haven't you? Do you think your chance of going through has gone now?
We'll learn from our mistakes.

Of course this was a big blow for us. We gave up easy possession too often and then had to work incredibly hard to get the ball back. We couldn't get a grip on the game at all. But we know where we have to improve, and we'll go into the next game determined to prove people wrong.
We'll give it a go in the second leg.

This was a real setback, of course. Credit to %1s. They completely dominated the game. But, if we can improve, we can still give it a go in the second leg, I think we can give them problems when we go forward. We have to be positive. And we have to score the first goal!
It's going to be difficult now.

When you play the first leg at home, it's so important to take a lead into the away game. But we came unstuck today. We're proud to represent %1s, though, so we certainly won't give up on the tie. Let's hope we can achieve something special at their place.
Is that any hope gone now?
That was a pretty comprehensive defeat for your team. Do you think your chances of going through have gone now? Or can your boys pull off something remarkable in the second leg?
We were poor and paid for it.

It's a shock to the system, for sure. We really had our hands full against a very good team. And we were shocking defensively. So, of course, we've given ourselves a lot to do in the second leg. But if the boys can get a grip on the game early? Let's see. We'll keep going, that's for sure.
We'll have to create more.

To be honest, %1s dominated most of the game. They were very impressive. But if our lads can get on the front foot in the second leg, we can show what we're capable of as an attacking force. We have to be more creative. It's going to take something special from us but we'll give it a go.
We have a lot to do, that's for sure!

That wasn't a %1s performance at all. We couldn't get close to them all game. We'll struggle to go through. But we've got professional pride to play for now. It's going to be difficult, but let's see if we can pull off something special at home.
A narrow defeat. Where does that leave the tie balanced?
That was a narrow defeat but we all know how strong your %1s team is at home. How will you approach the second leg? Do you think you can turn the tie round?
I'm confident about our chances.
We can definitely be better than we were here. Remember we'll have our fans behind us in the second leg and that always lifts the team. We'll need to play very well but I think we can go through.
We need to put them under pressure.

We struggled to make any impression on this first leg. %1s defended really well. Let's see how it goes in front of our own supporters, though. If we can put some pressure on them, I think the lads have enough quality to still turn the tie in our favour.
We seemed scared of the occasion.

We just didn't seem to believe in ourselves, as if the occasion was too big for us. The opposition were first into tackles and then played around us too easily. But I know we can be better than that. Let's make sure we're the team on the front foot in the second leg and then see what happens.
Does that draw give you the advantage now?
Does that draw in the away leg mean your %1s are favourites to go through now? How will you approach the second game back at your place?
A clean sheet would have been better.

That was pretty brutal, wasn't it? A very physical battle out there. I thought we were the better team, though. If we'd been a bit more on our toes in a couple of key moments, we could have come away with a win. Let's go one better now in the home game.
Let's be stronger at home.
Let's be stronger at home.

We let ourselves get bullied a bit, didn't we? It was a very physical contest. But If we can be stronger in that part of the game at home, I hope we've got enough quality in the team to give us the edge. We've got a big chance now to go through.

We let ourselves get bullied a bit, didn't we? It was a very physical contest. But If we can be stronger in that part of the game at home, I hope we've got enough quality in the team to give us the edge. We've got a big chance now to go through.
I think we're the better team.

I thought we did a lot of things well here and, with a bit of luck, we could have come away with a win. But we're in a decent position. I think we're the better of the two sides. We have to prove that now in the next game.
Does that draw give them the advantage?
You must have hoped you could earn an advantage to take away from home in the next leg. How frustrated are you that you weren't stronger defensively? Are your opponents favourites to go through now?
Our defensive work has to improve.

This is a tie between two very evenly-matched sides. The game could have gone either way. The lads worked hard the whole 90 minutes but didn't get their rewards. And, yes, we have to be better defensively. But we won't mind being underdogs. I still think our spirit can see us through.
Our attacking quality can win it for us.
Our attacking quality can win it for us.

This wasn't what we were hoping for in our game at home but we're definitely not out of it yet. The players know they'll have to find a little more creativity in the second leg. If they do that, I think we've got enough quality in the team to see us through to the semis.

This wasn't what we were hoping for in our game at home but we're definitely not out of it yet. The players know they'll have to find a little more creativity in the second leg. If they do that, I think we've got enough quality in the team to see us through to the semis.
We've made it difficult for ourselves.

It's fair to say we let ourselves down today. That wasn't the performance or the result we'd been hoping for. But it's not over yet. If we can get the first goal in the away leg then I still think we can reach the semis.
Is that a pretty good result away from home?
So, %1s travel home with a draw and a clean sheet. There's a place in the semi-final at stake. Can you find a goal or two with your own crowd behind you?
I believe in our players.

I have to be happy with how we played and with the result here. I know the atmosphere will be fantastic for the second leg. If we can strike early and get the crowd behind us at home, I think we can definitely make the semi-finals.
We probably could have won.

A goalless draw away from home isn't a bad result. Things just didn't fall for us in the important moments. A bit of luck and I think we actually could have won today. With the crowd behind us in the home leg, I hope we'll have our shooting boots on and be able to finish the job.
We want to deliver something special.

A goalless draw here gives us a fantastic chance of reaching the semis. We have to get a grip on the home game early now and, if we do that, I think we can give our supporters something special to celebrate.
A frustrating game for you. Can you still make the semis?

%1s usually find a goal or two in home games but the opposition defended very well here and you had to settle for the draw. It must have been frustrating for you, as it was for the fans. How do you rate your semi-final chances now?
We can go there and win.

We looked a well-organised side out there. To be honest, I always felt we'd go and find at least one goal to take into the away leg. But the luck wasn't with us, I guess. Another good performance from the boys in the next game, though, and I still think we can go through.
The ball wouldn't bounce for us.

They defended well but I though we were the better team and deserved to win. Yes, maybe we could have forced the issue a little more when we were in possession. But I've got a feeling we'll have more room to play on the counter away from home. That could make all the difference.
Not scoring is a let-down.

We let ourselves down a bit. I was sure we could score in front of our own fans and take a lead into the second leg. But I guess we're just going to have to do it the hard way now. Let's be positive. There's a place in the semi-final at stake, after all.
A brilliant win. Surely you're through now?

That must be as well as %1s have played away from home at any stage of the competition. You couldn't have asked for much more from your team. Do you feel you've already got one foot in the semi-final?
We can still improve in this tie.

One or two of our senior players were absolutely inspirational tonight. Strong and disciplined. Real leaders. None of the boys shirked a single tackle out there either. But I think we've got room to improve. Let's be professional and make sure the home game is one to remember for our fans. They deserve it.
We want to give our fans something to celebrate.

This was a fantastic result for us and we've definitely given ourselves every chance of reaching the semis. Let's make sure we're switched on defensively in the next game. Then we can express ourselves as an attacking force and really give our fans something to get excited about.
Let's just keep our heads.

Yes, that was a performance to be proud of and we definitely weren't flattered by the scoreline. We have to make sure we prepare properly for the next game now. If we play at that level again, our fans will be celebrating a place in the semi-finals, without a doubt.
A hard-fought win. Are you favourites for the semis now?

You must be proud of your team. With a place in the semi-finals at stake, you've come away against a very difficult opponent and managed to secure a win. Is it just a matter of keeping your heads now?
A great result but it's only half-time.

If I was sitting in the opposing dugout, I'd be admitting only one team deserved to win this first leg. But I'd also be telling my team that it's not over yet. I know we'll have to prepare well and be at our best again if we're going to make sure of a place in the semis.
It's definitely not over yet.

Great performance and a great result for us. But we can't be sure it'll be enough. Even with our home crowd behind us, we know these opponents can still make life difficult. We've plenty of work to do if we're going to reach the semi-final.
We still need to focus on our jobs.

It was a tight game and I'm very happy that we came out of it with a lead. The lads were great but I hope they realise they'll have to be on their toes again in the home leg if we're going to reach the semi-final. We have to focus on getting the job done.

It was a tight game and I'm very happy that we came out of it with a lead. The lads were great but I hope they realise they'll have to be on their toes again in the home leg if we're going to reach the semi-final. We have to focus on getting the job done.
After a pretty convincing win, are you favourites now?
%1s fans will be looking forward to the second leg now. To bring home a two-goal advantage from the first game is a big step towards the semi-final, surely. Are you confident you can finish the job?
Let's concentrate and make sure.

We were good value for the win here and a two-goal advantage is a big plus. But we have to keep our heads. It won't be an easy game at our place. If they score the first goal and our supporters get nervous then anything might happen. Let's focus!
We have to finish the job.

Of course this win puts us in a very strong position. We were well-organised in this first leg: the discipline and commitment out there earned us the victory, that's for sure. Let's have more of the same and finish the job in front of our own fans. We all want to celebrate reaching a semi-final.
I'm not going to speculate.

That was a great win and I'm not going to try being clever here. We've put ourselves in a great position, obviously. I'm not going to speculate about how the second leg will go, but if the lads go into it with the same attitude and spirit, I'm confident we can reach the semi-finals now.

That was a great win and I'm not going to try being clever here. We've put ourselves in a great position, obviously. I'm not going to speculate about how the second leg will go, but if the lads go into it with the same attitude and spirit, I'm confident we can reach the semi-finals now.
Does the two-goal advantage put you in the driving seat?

I think %1s supporters enjoyed the game. Definitely, the extra goal made all the difference to the atmosphere around the ground at full-time. Are you pretty confident the boys can reach the %2s semi-final now?
There's still a job to do.

We started the game really well and I think that got the crowd going. We need more of the same from our players in the away leg now. We must start well again because, if the opposition score first, the tie would be wide open again.
We'll need to be resilient again.

I was very pleased with the mental strength we showed here. All over the pitch, the boys were outstanding. But we're only halfway there. We'll have to be disciplined and resilient again in the away leg if we want to be sure of a place in the semis.
The tie should be over now.

We've put ourselves in a strong position, obviously. But I feel frustrated, to be honest. If we'd been a bit more clinical, this tie could have been out of sight. I want us to attack again away from home. If we score the first goal, we'll be into the semis, I'm sure.

We've put ourselves in a strong position, obviously. But I feel frustrated, to be honest. If we'd been a bit more clinical, this tie could have been out of sight. I want us to attack again away from home. If we score the first goal, we'll be into the semis, I'm sure.
Have your team done enough?

That was the narrowest of wins for your %1s team. But there's not much to choose between the two sides. Are you confident you'll be strong enough to meet the challenge in the away leg and get into the semis?
We'll have to be mentally strong.

I'm very pleased with the performance and any kind of win was going to give us the advantage. It's going to be hard away from home, though. They'll have their crowd behind them. We'll need to be mentally strong if we want to go through.
I hope we've done enough.

Of course it's not over yet, but we deserved this win and maybe we've already done enough. The lads were excellent, kept driving forward. Another performance like today and that will see us into the semi-final, I believe.
I'd have liked another goal!

We had home advantage and so I'd have liked us to win by more to be comfortable. But it is what it is. We've left ourselves work to do. The lads will have to be at their absolute best now if we're going to reach the semi-finals.
Your forwards made their mark, didn't they?

%1s are strong at home and so the win was no surprise. But I'm not sure anyone could have predicted how convincing the victory would be. Your goalscorers have given you a great chance of reaching the semi-finals now, haven't they?
The team loves to attack.

A great win, yes. But we know we'll be put under pressure in the away leg. If our defending is as disciplined as it was here, I'm confident we can go through. If we're strong on that side, we can free up our attacking players to go and do their stuff. Honestly? I think we could win the second leg, too.
We know what we'll have to do.

That's a great result and the goals have given us a great chance of reaching the semi-finals now. We'll have to be ready for them to put pressure on us at their place. It'll be up to the lads to stand up strong and make sure we see the tie through.
We're almost there!

We'll need to be professional about our work in the second leg. We were the better team here but it'll be different at their place. Let's keep our heads and not give them any encouragement. We're almost there now!
